3. Explicit Permission Required for All Uses Beyond Personal, Non-Commercial Use

3.1 No Implied Permission
No rights, licenses, or permissions, express or implied, are granted to the Licensee except for the explicit, personal, and non-commercial use as outlined in this Agreement. All other uses of the Licensed Works, including but not limited to any commercial or public use, require express written permission from the Licensor.

3.2 Written Permission Only
For the avoidance of doubt, any use, reference, reproduction, or distribution of the Licensed Works that falls outside the scope of this Agreement, or otherwise violates its terms, will require explicit written approval from the Licensor. All requests for permission must be submitted in writing, and the Licensor retains the sole discretion to approve or deny any such requests.

4. Attribution and Acknowledgment

4.1 Attribution Requirement
In the event that the Licensor grants permission to the Licensee to use the Licensed Works, proper attribution must be provided to the Licensor in the form and manner specified by the Licensor. This includes the following:

